5000|$|Silanes {{can also}} {{incorporate}} the same functional groups as alkanes, e.g. -OH, {{to make a}} silanol (an analogue of alcohol) or a halogen to make a <b>silicon</b> <b>halide</b> (an analogue of alkyl halide). There is (in principle) a silicon analogue for all carbon alkanes derivatives. Like carbon, there also exists silicocations, an important class is the silanyliums, of which simplest member is the silylium ion (...) [...]|$|E
