30|$|Examples of {{solution}} routes are sparser {{and involve}} {{the reduction of}} a <b>silicon</b> <b>halide</b> (SiCl 4, RSiCl 3) by a strong reducing agent [9], butyl-lithium, naphthalides [10, 11, 12] or hydrides [13, 14], in presence of a surfactant to limit the nanoparticles growth and coalescence but the surfactant shell impedes their use for electrochemical applications. Alternatively, Si nanowires are electrochemically deposited by step-edge decoration of highly oriented pyrolytic graphite (HOPG) from a platting solution of SiCl 4 in aprotic ionic liquid [15].|$|E
